Pre-Game Insights: Guy Bruhn's Pick: Take St. Louis
Others: The St. Louis Cardinals are headed to Yankee Stadium on Sunday where they will attempt to defeat the New York Yankees (78-56).
The expected starting pitchers will be Miles Mikolas and Nestor Cortes Jr.
The St. Louis Cardinals have 3,578 putouts on the year, as well as 1,262 assists and 59 errors.
The Yankees have turned 90 double plays and have accounted for a fielding rate of.983 (24th in baseball).
The New York pitching staff have yielded 552 runs this season while holding an ERA of 3.75 (500 earned runs conceded).
Cortes Jr has surrendered 485 base hits and he has 555 strikeouts in 548 innings pitched.
